Quick Start with 3 steps
1. Hold the binoculars with both hands and looking at a distant object.
Carefully and slowly move the binocular tubes downward or upward Until left and right fields are correctly aligned.
You'll See them are forming an oval circle in your sight.
2. It's now focused on your left eye and you will have to close your right eye. Look at an object through the left eyepiece with your left eye.
Rotate focusing ring until your left eye sees a sharp image of it.
3. It's now close to your left eye. Looking through the right eye and right eyepiece of the binoculars, adjust the diopter to focus the image of the object.
Rotate the diopter to get the final image.
